### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

router

### Description

I have a canActivateFn, I inject it a service that, at some point in my app, I change it's property values. But, on canActivateFn doesn't get the updated values, seems like it create a new instance service instead get singleton instance

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

For example

```
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class MyService {
  propertyA: string | null
}
```

```
export const canActivateFn: CanActivateFn = (next: ActivatedRouteSnapshot, state: RouterStateSnapshot) => {
  const myService = inject(MyService)

  console.log(myService.propertyA) // Always null
}
```

at some point, I execute `doStuff()` function

```
export class SomeService {
  myService = inject(MyService)

  doStuff () {
    myService.propertyA = 'Hello World!';
  }
}
```

```
export const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    loadComponent: () => import('...'),
    canActivate: [otherGuard],
    children: [
      {
        path: 'path1',
        loadComponent: () => import('...')
      },
      {
        path: 'path2',
        canActivate: [canActivateFn], // this is the guard
        loadComponent: () => import('...')
      }
    ]
  }
]
```




